[Interminable]

00:04:30.080 --> 00:04:30.920
Brother!

00:04:35.520 --> 00:04:36.920
Hello, Chai.

00:04:37.960 --> 00:04:39.760
I didn’t know you’re also here.

00:04:40.680 --> 00:04:41.640
Hello, Kaew.

00:04:42.480 --> 00:04:44.000
Ruedee told me she wanted to see you.

00:04:44.560 --> 00:04:46.800
So, I volunteered to be her driver.

00:04:47.400 --> 00:04:49.880
She said she has something important to talk to you in private.

00:04:53.360 --> 00:04:54.520
It’s a beautiful house.

00:04:57.520 --> 00:04:59.880
Please come inside then.

00:05:00.560 --> 00:05:01.120
Yes.

00:05:16.520 --> 00:05:18.080
You really live here.

00:05:32.480 --> 00:05:33.680
Drive!

00:05:46.480 --> 00:05:47.920
Please come in.

00:05:47.960 --> 00:05:48.600
Thank you.

00:06:06.200 --> 00:06:07.800
Wait, who are you?

00:06:08.400 --> 00:06:10.520
It’s me who should be asking that. Who are you?

00:06:11.360 --> 00:06:14.440
How dare you come in and walk around this white house so leisurely?

00:06:16.040 --> 00:06:16.840
Saen.

00:06:18.560 --> 00:06:20.160
Have some manners.

00:06:21.360 --> 00:06:22.600
He’s a guest…

00:06:23.160 --> 00:06:25.160
who came uninvited.

00:06:34.159 --> 00:06:35.240
Chai,

00:06:35.920 --> 00:06:37.760
this is Khun Yai and Saen.

00:06:39.960 --> 00:06:41.480
They also live here.

00:06:43.200 --> 00:06:44.000
I see.

00:06:45.440 --> 00:06:46.240
Hello.

00:06:48.960 --> 00:06:50.480
A pleasure to meet you.

00:06:59.400 --> 00:07:03.400
I’m Chai, an older brother of Ruedee...

00:07:03.880 --> 00:07:05.600
Kaewta’s best friend.

00:07:06.240 --> 00:07:09.120
I just came back from Amsterdam.

00:07:16.200 --> 00:07:19.600
Should we sit down and talk?

00:07:21.400 --> 00:07:22.200
Sure.

00:07:31.880 --> 00:07:34.159
This house is so beautiful, Kaew.

00:07:36.440 --> 00:07:38.520
It’s called a white house…

00:07:39.120 --> 00:07:42.680
because the entire house is painted white.

00:07:44.720 --> 00:07:46.200
Looking this impressive,

00:07:47.000 --> 00:07:49.240
I guess the owner of this house…

00:07:49.640 --> 00:07:51.760
must surely have it built with love.

00:07:57.680 --> 00:08:03.560
Well, the owner had this house built to live with his lover.

00:08:08.360 --> 00:08:09.640
But somehow…

00:08:10.040 --> 00:08:12.040
it also looks quite eerie.

00:08:21.400 --> 00:08:22.520
Hello.

00:08:25.280 --> 00:08:27.200
You appear out of nowhere.

00:08:29.520 --> 00:08:30.480
Nanny Yam.

00:08:32.080 --> 00:08:33.760
She’s Nanny Yam.

00:08:36.039 --> 00:08:38.600
What do you mean by ‘eerie’, Mister?

00:08:40.760 --> 00:08:42.240
Well, I mean…

00:08:49.240 --> 00:08:55.080
I see you have another guest, so I’m bringing more drinks, Khun Kaew.

00:08:59.160 --> 00:09:00.640
Let me help.

00:09:03.320 --> 00:09:06.320
Thank you. I’m kind of thirsty right now.

00:09:17.040 --> 00:09:17.720
Why…

00:09:18.120 --> 00:09:20.640
Why is it so bitter?

00:09:21.920 --> 00:09:24.520
Of course it’s bitter. It’s giloy juice.

00:09:26.960 --> 00:09:32.160
Nanny Yam, do you usually welcome your guests with giloy juice?

00:09:32.880 --> 00:09:36.880
Giloy juice with honey is good for your health.

00:09:37.960 --> 00:09:40.880
But I’m afraid I must have forgotten to add honey.

00:09:41.800 --> 00:09:44.240
I’ll make you a new one then.

00:09:44.560 --> 00:09:47.400
That’s all right. I’m full now.

00:09:50.960 --> 00:09:52.200
Thank you, Nanny.

00:09:52.760 --> 00:09:55.040
Please leave the rest to me.

00:09:55.400 --> 00:09:56.560
You can go rest now.

00:09:57.360 --> 00:09:58.400
Yes.

00:10:04.120 --> 00:10:04.960
Kaew.

00:10:05.600 --> 00:10:09.440
Ruedee told me you’ve inherited this house from the previous owner, is that right?

00:10:10.040 --> 00:10:11.280
Yes.

00:10:12.080 --> 00:10:14.560
The previous owner of this house…

00:10:14.560 --> 00:10:16.640
is Chao Meun Samur Chairatch.

00:10:17.680 --> 00:10:22.120
I only found out recently that my father was his distant relative.

00:10:29.480 --> 00:10:31.440
But I think it’s strange, Kaew.

00:10:38.760 --> 00:10:44.040
If they were actually related, why had your father never mentioned about him before?

00:10:45.200 --> 00:10:47.120
Have you tried to verify it?

00:10:50.160 --> 00:10:52.080
My mother is the only relative I have left.

00:10:53.080 --> 00:10:58.000
Relatives on my father’s side are all gone. I don’t know where to…

00:10:59.520 --> 00:11:01.280
…get the information from.

00:11:02.160 --> 00:11:04.680
That makes it even stranger, Kaew.

00:11:05.240 --> 00:11:06.440
I think…

00:11:10.760 --> 00:11:11.720
How…

00:11:12.320 --> 00:11:14.560
How on earth did it fall down?

00:11:15.040 --> 00:11:16.040
Yeah.

00:11:16.640 --> 00:11:17.520
It gave me a fright.

00:11:20.080 --> 00:11:21.840
- Are you all right, Kaew?
- Yes.

00:11:40.760 --> 00:11:41.880
Brother?

00:11:42.240 --> 00:11:43.040
Yes? Yes!

00:11:44.080 --> 00:11:44.880
Yes? What is it?

00:11:45.000 --> 00:11:47.240
Are you all right? I’ve been calling you for a while.

00:11:48.400 --> 00:11:49.200
It’s…

00:11:52.840 --> 00:11:53.640
It’s nothing.

00:11:55.600 --> 00:12:00.000
Let’s go home then. We’ve left for quite some time now. Mother might be worried.

00:12:01.520 --> 00:12:02.320
Okay.

00:12:03.400 --> 00:12:06.040
Kaew, I’m leaving then.

00:12:07.480 --> 00:12:09.200
Okay, I’ll walk you out.

00:12:11.440 --> 00:12:15.040
Goodbye, Khun Yai. Goodbye, Saen.

00:12:20.040 --> 00:12:20.840
Be careful.

00:12:22.080 --> 00:12:22.880
Let’s go.

00:12:36.840 --> 00:12:38.600
Can’t he walk himself to the car?

00:12:39.480 --> 00:12:40.640
Why must Kaew walk him out?

00:12:46.120 --> 00:12:49.800
What are you standing there for? Clean it up.

00:12:51.000 --> 00:12:51.800
Yes, sir.

00:13:05.080 --> 00:13:07.640
Has your uninvited guest gone back home?

00:13:10.480 --> 00:13:12.040
Who do you mean, Khun Yai?

00:13:12.920 --> 00:13:13.920
Ruedee?

00:13:16.480 --> 00:13:17.520
I mean…

00:13:18.000 --> 00:13:20.400
the one who kept walking all over this place.

00:13:21.160 --> 00:13:22.600
No manners.

00:13:24.720 --> 00:13:26.720
If you mean Chai,

00:13:27.520 --> 00:13:29.960
he is my friend’s–Ruedee’s brother.

00:13:30.600 --> 00:13:32.520
Not an uninvited guest.

00:13:33.760 --> 00:13:38.200
Nonetheless, he shouldn’t have walked around without asking for permission from the owner first.

00:13:40.040 --> 00:13:41.960
He just wanted to take a look around the house.

00:13:43.280 --> 00:13:44.680
Please don’t take it seriously.

00:13:48.760 --> 00:13:49.800
Are you sure…

00:13:50.840 --> 00:13:52.480
…that he only wanted to look at the house?

00:13:53.920 --> 00:13:54.720
Yes.

00:13:55.800 --> 00:13:57.080
Do you have a problem with that?

00:13:57.360 --> 00:13:58.720
He’s clearly interested in…

00:14:07.520 --> 00:14:09.120
Don’t ever invite him here again.

00:14:14.480 --> 00:14:15.640
This is an order.

00:14:25.360 --> 00:14:26.720
What’s wrong with him?

00:14:37.560 --> 00:14:40.480
Make sure you prepare everything as ordered.

00:14:40.800 --> 00:14:41.600
Yes, Miss.

00:14:50.960 --> 00:14:53.200
Brother, what are you thinking?

00:14:54.880 --> 00:14:55.720
Ruedee.

00:14:57.080 --> 00:14:58.600
Who is Khun Yai?

00:14:59.600 --> 00:15:01.440
Why is he also staying at the white house?

00:15:02.200 --> 00:15:06.400
Kaew said he’s a friend of the previous owner.

00:15:06.400 --> 00:15:08.800
That’s why he’s allowed to live there.

00:15:17.400 --> 00:15:20.520
Is something bothering your mind, Brother?

00:15:22.000 --> 00:15:23.560
I think he’s quite off.

00:15:24.600 --> 00:15:25.440
How?

00:15:27.760 --> 00:15:29.600
I can't point out exactly.

00:15:31.640 --> 00:15:38.360
Actually, I also feel the same.

00:15:39.040 --> 00:15:43.680
I also find it strange how he looks exactly like that man in Kaew’s dream.

00:15:45.000 --> 00:15:46.720
In Kaew’s dream?

00:15:47.560 --> 00:15:48.600
What do you mean?

00:15:49.320 --> 00:15:50.120
Well…

00:15:50.120 --> 00:15:55.080
Kaew used to tell me he had been dreaming of this man for a long time.

00:15:55.080 --> 00:15:58.320
Until he came to live at the white house.

00:15:58.320 --> 00:16:00.880
Before that, he wasn’t able to draw any portrait.

00:16:00.880 --> 00:16:04.320
But after he’s moved in, he could suddenly draw the portrait of this man.

00:16:05.000 --> 00:16:06.280
Then what?

00:16:06.640 --> 00:16:10.040
It turns out that man in his dream also exists in real life.

00:16:10.360 --> 00:16:11.680
It’s Khun Yai.

00:16:13.280 --> 00:16:14.560
What a coincidence.

00:16:17.760 --> 00:16:20.920
Please excuse me then, I have to go to the kitchen.

00:16:21.160 --> 00:16:22.040
Okay.

00:16:28.040 --> 00:16:29.400
The man from his dream?

00:16:30.680 --> 00:16:33.120
Is it really possible to have such coincidence?

00:16:48.440 --> 00:16:50.600
Where are Sin and Saen?

00:16:51.680 --> 00:16:53.800
I thought they would come and give alms to the monk together.

00:17:03.720 --> 00:17:06.640
Can I join you in this merit-making?

00:17:09.880 --> 00:17:10.960
Go ahead.

00:17:11.839 --> 00:17:13.200
Thank you.

00:17:17.400 --> 00:17:18.920
Oh, here he comes.

00:17:25.359 --> 00:17:26.560
Greetings, Luangta.

00:17:26.800 --> 00:17:27.800
Bless you.

00:18:27.000 --> 00:18:28.480
So, the time has come.

00:18:33.120 --> 00:18:36.360
Luangta, I have a question.

00:18:37.840 --> 00:18:40.000
What is it that you want to know?

00:18:41.360 --> 00:18:45.880
Sharing merits in this life to be together in the next – is it true or just a belief…

00:18:45.880 --> 00:18:48.520
…that it would make us be together in every life?

00:18:53.040 --> 00:18:54.640
If you keep making merits together…

00:18:55.440 --> 00:18:57.360
and always observe the five precepts,

00:18:57.880 --> 00:18:59.920
you will always find each other.

00:19:00.920 --> 00:19:04.920
I see. So it’s not just a belief then.

00:19:07.320 --> 00:19:08.520
Time to receive blessings.

00:19:18.640 --> 00:19:28.840
(The Buddhist chant to give blessings to merit makers)

00:19:35.440 --> 00:19:36.800
Bless you.

00:19:36.920 --> 00:19:38.720
Amen.

00:19:47.800 --> 00:19:49.160
If that’s the case,

00:19:49.920 --> 00:19:54.560
can I join you to give alms to the monk every day?

00:19:58.720 --> 00:19:59.840
Of course.

00:20:15.240 --> 00:20:16.560
What’s wrong with him?

00:20:30.920 --> 00:20:33.280
We’ve been through a lot before we could be together.

00:20:35.680 --> 00:20:37.680
I won’t give up so easily.

00:20:53.440 --> 00:20:54.680
My brother,

00:21:02.240 --> 00:21:03.720
are you back?

00:21:04.360 --> 00:21:05.520
Sophee.

00:21:06.600 --> 00:21:10.520
I’ve been waiting here since afternoon. No one told me you’d be home this late.

00:21:11.800 --> 00:21:13.120
I had some matters to attend to.

00:21:13.600 --> 00:21:17.720
You could’ve asked someone to call for me. Why trouble yourself like this?

00:21:20.000 --> 00:21:23.120
You haven’t come to eat with us at the main house for many days.

00:21:23.400 --> 00:21:26.920
Father is also worried something might happen to you.

00:21:28.280 --> 00:21:29.520
I’m fine.

00:21:30.160 --> 00:21:33.160
I’m just tired. I’ll feel better after I get some rest.

00:21:33.960 --> 00:21:37.800
Then, I’ll go prepare some tonic and bring it to you here.

00:21:38.040 --> 00:21:39.360
I’m fine indeed.

00:21:39.720 --> 00:21:41.760
It’s late, you should leave.

00:21:41.760 --> 00:21:44.440
Our servants might be gossiping about it.

00:21:45.440 --> 00:21:48.120
You’ve only seen my face for less than a minute and you’re shooing me away.

00:21:48.320 --> 00:21:50.080
Fine, I’ll go back to my place.

00:21:51.000 --> 00:21:53.280
I’m just an adopted son.

00:21:54.040 --> 00:21:55.440
And you’re a lady.

00:21:55.920 --> 00:21:58.040
A man and a lady shouldn’t be too close to each other.

00:21:58.560 --> 00:21:59.920
Or people might talk badly about them.

00:22:01.080 --> 00:22:03.600
You don’t have to try to convince me with those reasons.

00:22:04.280 --> 00:22:05.560
I’m leaving.

00:22:06.200 --> 00:22:09.840
Please tell Father for me that I’ll pay him a visit tomorrow morning.

00:22:11.040 --> 00:22:13.120
Yes. Let’s go, Som.

00:22:14.080 --> 00:22:17.120
Yes, Miss. Please be careful and watch your steps.

00:22:18.320 --> 00:22:19.080
Let’s go, Saen.

00:22:19.080 --> 00:22:20.000
Yes, sir.

00:23:03.520 --> 00:23:05.080
Lady Chuichai…

00:23:07.520 --> 00:23:08.920
…is a guy?

00:23:43.040 --> 00:23:44.920
Do I really like men?

00:23:49.200 --> 00:23:52.200
You can resist anything in this world.

00:23:53.120 --> 00:23:56.040
But you shall never resist the yearning in your heart.

00:23:56.600 --> 00:23:59.080
You can break all the bonds there is in this world.

00:23:59.680 --> 00:24:02.600
But you shall never break the bond of love that is binding your heart.

00:24:11.120 --> 00:24:13.840
Khun Phra Nai, the servant Som would like to see you, sir.

00:24:15.560 --> 00:24:19.360
Khun Phra Nai is busy right now. You can leave your message with me.

00:24:20.000 --> 00:24:22.120
But what I’m going to tell him is…

00:24:22.200 --> 00:24:23.120
What do you want?

00:24:33.880 --> 00:24:34.680
Say it.

00:24:38.040 --> 00:24:42.960
A servant from Luang Sanor’s place has told me that Khun Luang would like to see you.

00:24:42.960 --> 00:24:46.360
It’s something important. That’s why I’m here to tell you, sir.

00:25:34.320 --> 00:25:39.560
Geez, he’s trying to get over it…why does it have to be now?

00:25:40.960 --> 00:25:42.280
You’re here, Khun Yai?

00:25:48.400 --> 00:25:51.640
You guys, let’s stop for a while.

00:25:56.000 --> 00:25:57.720
Again, Uncle?

00:25:58.320 --> 00:26:00.480
If we have to stop practising this often,

00:26:01.080 --> 00:26:06.080
wouldn’t you be embarrassed if we can’t dance properly in front of the audience?

00:26:06.640 --> 00:26:08.120
Geez, this brat.

00:26:08.280 --> 00:26:11.080
I have a guest, can’t you see?

00:26:13.520 --> 00:26:15.000
Good morning, Uncle.

00:26:15.160 --> 00:26:16.520
Bless you, son.

00:26:16.960 --> 00:26:18.680
Come in. Have a seat first.

00:26:20.160 --> 00:26:22.760
How are you, Khun Phra? Are you doing well?

00:26:23.880 --> 00:26:24.680
Yes.

00:26:28.400 --> 00:26:33.840
Oh, crap. Did I just pick a fight with a Lord?

00:26:35.160 --> 00:26:36.560
What was that, Kaew?

00:26:37.320 --> 00:26:39.400
Whom did you pick a fight with?

00:26:40.160 --> 00:26:41.600
Nothing.

00:26:45.120 --> 00:26:48.040
Khun Phra Nai is so handsome.

00:26:50.200 --> 00:26:51.480
Let’s go, Ruedee.

00:26:51.880 --> 00:26:54.000
We should prepare drinks for our guests.

00:26:54.760 --> 00:26:55.560
Okay.

00:27:05.920 --> 00:27:08.600
I have an important matter to talk to you.

00:27:14.440 --> 00:27:15.240
Khun Yai.

00:27:17.040 --> 00:27:18.080
Khun Yai!

00:27:19.600 --> 00:27:20.840
Yes, Uncle?

00:27:23.560 --> 00:27:25.920
The way I tried to woo him, didn’t it work?

00:27:27.800 --> 00:27:31.200
Do you mean, “Sharing merit in this life to be together in the next”?

00:27:32.600 --> 00:27:35.320
Damn you, Saen. You’re getting more brazen these days.

00:27:36.040 --> 00:27:37.680
My apologies, Khun Yai.

00:27:38.280 --> 00:27:41.640
But that Khun Kaew is a different person from this Khun Kaew.

00:27:43.040 --> 00:27:45.280
Yeah, you’re right.

00:27:46.120 --> 00:27:48.360
The era is also different.

00:27:49.560 --> 00:27:51.440
If you still use the same way to woo him,

00:27:51.600 --> 00:27:56.120
Khun Kaew might think you’re an outdated poet from the past.

00:27:59.920 --> 00:28:00.920
That’s true.

00:28:01.920 --> 00:28:03.840
I’m afraid I’ll have to change my tactic.

00:28:04.720 --> 00:28:05.960
Couldn’t agree more.

00:28:10.920 --> 00:28:11.920
Sin.

00:28:12.000 --> 00:28:12.800
Yes, Khun Kaew?

00:28:12.800 --> 00:28:14.280
Is there anything I can help?

00:28:14.480 --> 00:28:17.520
Why would you bother, Khun Kaew? Please let me do it.

00:28:18.520 --> 00:28:23.040
It’s fine. You can go dump the leaves in that basket.

00:28:23.680 --> 00:28:25.040
Let me take care of the rest.

00:28:25.600 --> 00:28:26.600
Are you sure?

00:28:27.680 --> 00:28:28.920
You’re so diligent, Khun Kaew.

00:28:29.640 --> 00:28:30.880
Okay then. Thank you!

00:28:55.600 --> 00:28:59.400
Is this the renowned white house of Chao Meun Samur Chairatch?

00:29:09.360 --> 00:29:10.640
Lady Sophee.

00:29:10.760 --> 00:29:14.600
Is this the renowned white house of Chao Meun Samur Chairatch?

00:29:14.760 --> 00:29:16.800
No! Nooo!

00:29:17.520 --> 00:29:18.800
Miss Sophee.

00:29:33.400 --> 00:29:34.880
Oh, shit.

00:29:44.200 --> 00:29:46.280
Aren’t you going to invite me into your house?

00:29:52.120 --> 00:29:52.920
This way please.

00:30:01.120 --> 00:30:03.400
Trouble, trouble! We have trouble!

00:30:03.840 --> 00:30:06.200
Watch your manners. Haven’t I told you many times already?

00:30:06.280 --> 00:30:09.760
Geez, Dad, this isn’t the time to complain. Do you know who’s just come?

00:30:10.560 --> 00:30:11.360
Who?

00:30:20.840 --> 00:30:22.080
Sophee.

00:30:41.680 --> 00:30:43.760
Why is Lady Sophee here?

00:30:44.440 --> 00:30:45.120
Yeah.

00:30:45.480 --> 00:30:46.960
I’d like to know that too.

00:30:51.640 --> 00:30:54.600
Will she be able to see us, Khun Yai?

00:30:59.680 --> 00:31:00.760
I don’t know.

00:31:01.960 --> 00:31:03.040
But if she does,

00:31:03.800 --> 00:31:06.680
it means she has also reincarnated…

00:31:06.680 --> 00:31:08.560
and probably can’t remember anything about her past life.

00:31:20.480 --> 00:31:22.040
How many people live here?

00:31:23.600 --> 00:31:25.080
Think carefully before you answer.

00:31:27.560 --> 00:31:31.240
There are Khun Kaew, his mother, and me.

00:31:32.000 --> 00:31:34.520
Oh, and also a couple of faithful servants.

00:31:35.000 --> 00:31:35.840
Sin!

00:31:37.360 --> 00:31:39.040
They are working in the back.

00:31:39.560 --> 00:31:41.960
Would you like me to introduce them to you now, Miss?

00:31:42.520 --> 00:31:43.320
No need.

00:31:43.640 --> 00:31:45.160
Where’s the house owner?

00:31:46.400 --> 00:31:48.240
The house owner right now…

00:31:48.920 --> 00:31:50.320
is Khun Kaewta.

00:31:53.280 --> 00:31:55.520
Lady Sophee can’t see us, Khun Yai.

00:31:56.440 --> 00:31:57.560
That might be because…

00:31:58.280 --> 00:32:01.120
Sophee and I have no more karma left to share.

00:32:13.760 --> 00:32:15.480
Sorry to keep you waiting.

00:32:18.040 --> 00:32:19.320
This snack…

00:32:19.320 --> 00:32:22.080
is made by my mother fresh from the oven.

00:32:25.680 --> 00:32:26.480
Thanks.

00:32:29.720 --> 00:32:34.760
From what I’ve learnt, this white house used to belong to Chao Meun Samur Chairatch.

00:32:35.480 --> 00:32:37.800
How come you’re here in his place?

00:32:38.520 --> 00:32:41.640
I have inherited this house from the previous owner.

00:32:42.640 --> 00:32:44.280
I’m his relative.

00:32:46.920 --> 00:32:47.920
Is that so?

00:32:48.640 --> 00:32:52.160
You, a relative of a high-ranking nobleman?

00:32:56.280 --> 00:32:57.760
On my father’s side (of the family).

00:32:58.840 --> 00:33:00.320
That’s what they told me.

00:33:01.400 --> 00:33:02.240
Are you sure?

00:33:10.960 --> 00:33:12.400
Pardon me,

00:33:12.400 --> 00:33:16.720
but what matter brings you here?

00:33:18.120 --> 00:33:23.400
I suppose Ruedee has already told you
how I’d like you to draw my portrait, hasn’t she?

00:33:27.320 --> 00:33:27.840
Yes.

00:33:28.680 --> 00:33:29.560
But…

00:33:30.000 --> 00:33:32.720
I’m afraid I’ll have to turn down your request.

00:33:33.720 --> 00:33:36.400
Hasn’t Ruedee told you that I refused?

00:33:36.760 --> 00:33:41.200
She has. But I want to hear the reason from you in person. Why can’t you do it?

00:33:44.640 --> 00:33:47.440
I can’t draw a portrait of anyone.

00:33:49.120 --> 00:33:50.240
Don’t lie.

00:33:50.560 --> 00:33:52.200
I’ve seen your drawing before.

00:33:54.520 --> 00:33:56.640
Where did you see it?

00:33:57.560 --> 00:34:02.280
The university you’re studying at. My family is one of the land donors.

00:34:02.720 --> 00:34:06.280
I also fund a scholarship for top students.

00:34:06.280 --> 00:34:10.000
So, it’s not surprising that I’d know your professor.

00:34:13.159 --> 00:34:16.159
Here is the portrait that Kaewta drew, as you’ve ordered.

00:34:39.000 --> 00:34:41.679
What if I want to buy this drawing,

00:34:42.199 --> 00:34:43.800
will you sell it to me?

00:34:46.719 --> 00:34:48.760
Even though I was the one who asked my students to draw,

00:34:49.120 --> 00:34:51.520
I’m afraid I don’t own any of their works.

00:34:58.800 --> 00:35:00.320
A small token for your help.

00:35:00.840 --> 00:35:02.600
Ten times more than last time.

00:35:05.840 --> 00:35:07.760
I guess we’re settled then.

00:35:22.840 --> 00:35:25.480
I miss you so much, my love.

00:35:37.840 --> 00:35:39.160
Kaewta.

00:35:43.000 --> 00:35:45.080
Does this mean…

00:35:47.360 --> 00:35:49.840
Kaewta has met him already?

00:35:51.080 --> 00:35:54.720
You saw my drawing from Ajarn Kitti?

00:35:55.080 --> 00:35:58.440
Yes, now how else are you going to lie about it?

00:35:59.800 --> 00:36:01.400
I’m not lying.

00:36:03.720 --> 00:36:05.920
I really can’t draw a portrait.

00:36:07.240 --> 00:36:08.120
I…

00:36:08.120 --> 00:36:09.880
I’ve tried.

00:36:09.960 --> 00:36:11.320
What about the portrait of my…

00:36:13.200 --> 00:36:14.520
of that man?

00:36:17.000 --> 00:36:20.840
That’s the first and only portrait I could draw.

00:36:23.120 --> 00:36:26.840
Is there such a thing like that? How ridiculous.

00:36:31.160 --> 00:36:32.880
If you don’t believe it,

00:36:34.720 --> 00:36:36.440
then I have nothing else to say.

00:36:37.560 --> 00:36:42.520
But of course, I believe you. You’ve firmly insisted it like that.

00:36:43.280 --> 00:36:47.280
Anyway, how’s that man in the drawing special to you?

00:36:47.280 --> 00:36:49.680
Why is he the only portrait you can draw?

00:36:54.240 --> 00:36:55.640
I also…

00:36:56.120 --> 00:36:57.800
don’t understand it either.

00:37:00.600 --> 00:37:01.880
Where did you see him?

00:37:05.280 --> 00:37:05.920
Sin!

00:37:05.920 --> 00:37:06.680
Well…

00:37:07.680 --> 00:37:10.840
Where is it? I’m asking you, answer me.

00:37:16.440 --> 00:37:17.360
Sin!

00:37:19.200 --> 00:37:20.000
It’s…

00:37:20.520 --> 00:37:21.960
It was in his dream.

00:37:24.040 --> 00:37:25.600
Khun Kaewta told me…

00:37:26.080 --> 00:37:29.800
he saw that man in his dream, Miss.

00:37:30.440 --> 00:37:31.240
Really?

00:37:34.280 --> 00:37:35.080
Yes.

00:37:36.880 --> 00:37:39.120
I drew it from what I saw my dream.

00:37:44.040 --> 00:37:48.160
Even in a dream, you could still see my man?

00:37:48.240 --> 00:37:49.960
Are you trying to brag about it?

00:37:50.400 --> 00:37:53.560
Such a pretentious bitch since past life.

00:38:12.800 --> 00:38:15.480
Is her visit still bothering your mind, Khun Yai?

00:38:19.080 --> 00:38:20.960
Today when Sophee came,

00:38:21.280 --> 00:38:22.680
I could feel something was off.

00:38:23.920 --> 00:38:25.120
What do you mean?

00:38:26.360 --> 00:38:29.000
Why did she want to know how many people live here?

00:38:33.200 --> 00:38:34.160
You’re right!

00:38:34.880 --> 00:38:38.600
Miss Sophee also asked Sin about the owner of this place.

00:38:40.000 --> 00:38:42.920
And even asked Kaewta about my portrait.

00:38:47.040 --> 00:38:48.560
She’s certainly suspicious.

00:39:18.720 --> 00:39:20.440
You’re here?

00:39:23.960 --> 00:39:24.720
Yes.

00:39:27.240 --> 00:39:30.480
I have an urgent matter that needs your advice, Khun Luang…

00:39:31.920 --> 00:39:33.280
mean, Luangta.

00:39:36.600 --> 00:39:39.280
His enemy in the past life has finally found him, hasn’t she?

00:39:41.960 --> 00:39:43.200
You knew?

00:39:44.960 --> 00:39:45.760
So…

00:39:47.360 --> 00:39:49.080
What should I do then?

00:39:51.720 --> 00:39:56.480
Karma has a mysterious power. No one can ever escape the hands of Karma.

00:39:57.040 --> 00:40:04.320
The only thing you can do is be mindful, and brace yourself for whatever that will happen.

00:40:20.920 --> 00:40:22.360
I understand.

00:40:53.160 --> 00:40:55.200
I’m curious now, Som.

00:40:57.040 --> 00:40:58.960
About what, my lady?

00:40:59.640 --> 00:41:04.400
I’m curious what exactly it is that Luang Sanor is trying to teach his dancers.

00:41:05.360 --> 00:41:09.480
Is it perhaps for them to seduce the men?

00:41:10.080 --> 00:41:10.880
I believe so too.

00:41:11.080 --> 00:41:12.560
Don’t talk about him like that.

00:41:12.880 --> 00:41:15.480
Why can’t I? It’s the truth.

00:41:17.000 --> 00:41:21.280
A classical dance is an art of training and worshipping the masters.

00:41:21.280 --> 00:41:23.560
It’s something delicate and graceful…

00:41:23.560 --> 00:41:25.880
…invented by the mankind.

00:41:27.000 --> 00:41:28.360
Those who are civilized…

00:41:29.000 --> 00:41:32.320
…shall never look down on such a prestigious art.

00:41:34.000 --> 00:41:35.400
Civilized?

00:41:36.480 --> 00:41:40.760
Look down? Prestigious? A person like you doesn’t need those things.

00:41:43.200 --> 00:41:44.320
Your hair…

00:41:47.000 --> 00:41:48.800
It’s so important to you, isn’t it?

00:41:50.480 --> 00:41:52.840
Here you go, my lady.

00:41:54.240 --> 00:41:56.480
No! No! Don’t! Don’t!

00:41:56.600 --> 00:41:57.480
No! Don’t!

00:41:58.480 --> 00:42:00.400
No! No!

00:42:01.440 --> 00:42:02.320
Don’t!

00:42:02.960 --> 00:42:04.600
No!

00:42:04.600 --> 00:42:05.960
No!

00:42:06.560 --> 00:42:08.280
Filthy bitch.

00:42:11.680 --> 00:42:13.000
Don’t!

00:42:34.520 --> 00:42:35.960
What kind of dream is that?

00:42:37.160 --> 00:42:38.880
Why does it feel so real?

00:43:28.640 --> 00:43:29.680
Who is it?

00:43:30.040 --> 00:43:31.760
Is it Saen or Sin?

00:43:32.280 --> 00:43:34.480
How do they know I want to draw?

00:43:38.040 --> 00:43:38.840
Khun Yai.

00:43:42.440 --> 00:43:44.680
Don’t forget to draw the portrait of that person you’re thinking of.

00:43:50.360 --> 00:43:51.760
I beg your pardon.

00:43:53.240 --> 00:43:56.760
If you miss someone, draw that person.

00:44:22.800 --> 00:44:24.480
But if you don’t know whom to draw,

00:44:25.480 --> 00:44:27.480
I’m always here to model for you.

00:45:37.880 --> 00:45:39.520
What was I thinking?

00:45:41.640 --> 00:45:42.920
So?

00:45:43.800 --> 00:45:46.560
Am I fortunate enough to model for your drawing?

00:45:54.560 --> 00:45:55.400
Of course.

00:45:57.480 --> 00:45:58.280
Go ahead.

00:46:34.880 --> 00:46:36.720
Why are you blushing?

00:46:36.920 --> 00:46:37.840
Is it hot?

00:46:38.520 --> 00:46:39.960
Or are you not feeling well?

00:46:42.800 --> 00:46:43.600
Nothing.

00:46:45.560 --> 00:46:46.560
I’m fine.

00:46:47.920 --> 00:46:48.720
Hey.

00:46:49.640 --> 00:46:51.240
You look even redder now.

00:46:51.920 --> 00:46:53.600
How could you say you’re fine?

00:46:56.080 --> 00:46:58.320
Your choices of words are quite odd.

00:46:58.720 --> 00:47:00.400
Like those in an ancient book.

00:47:01.840 --> 00:47:03.800
I’m ancient indeed.

00:47:07.520 --> 00:47:09.080
I mean…

00:47:11.280 --> 00:47:13.320
My mind still remains in the ancient time.

00:47:15.600 --> 00:47:17.120
The time when we were still together.

00:47:18.480 --> 00:47:20.160
How could that be possible?

00:47:22.200 --> 00:47:23.720
We’ve just known each other.

00:47:27.840 --> 00:47:29.240
Have you given it a thought?

00:47:29.920 --> 00:47:32.360
Are you sure we’ve never met before?

00:47:55.280 --> 00:47:56.680
I’ve changed my mind.

00:47:59.400 --> 00:48:01.120
I’m going to read some books.

00:48:04.960 --> 00:48:06.040
Please excuse me.

00:48:19.600 --> 00:48:24.200
Karma has a mysterious power. No one can ever escape the hands of Karma.

00:48:24.560 --> 00:48:31.800
The only thing you can do is be mindful, and brace yourself for whatever that will happen.

00:48:34.160 --> 00:48:36.280
I hope you’ll remember me…

00:48:38.240 --> 00:48:39.880
before anything will happen.

00:49:01.080 --> 00:49:02.440
Have you given it a thought?

00:49:03.880 --> 00:49:05.760
Are you sure we’ve never met before?

00:49:09.640 --> 00:49:11.760
I’m sure this is the first time we met.

00:49:14.080 --> 00:49:15.520
Why would he want me to think about it again?

00:50:16.080 --> 00:50:17.800
Excuse me, sir.

00:54:08.960 --> 00:54:09.760
Khun Yai.

00:54:11.240 --> 00:54:12.440
I’m sorry.

00:54:46.760 --> 00:54:49.720
Will you draw for me and only me, my dear?

00:54:57.480 --> 00:54:58.400
Yes.

00:55:07.120 --> 00:55:08.200
Promise?

00:55:53.760 --> 00:55:55.480
When did I fall asleep?

00:56:15.000 --> 00:56:18.520
[Next Episode]
Why does Ajarn Kitti want you to take your drawing back today?

00:56:19.160 --> 00:56:20.440
I wonder too.

00:56:20.880 --> 00:56:22.560
There’s no one here.

00:56:26.280 --> 00:56:27.080
Kaew!

00:56:27.280 --> 00:56:28.000
Kaew!

00:56:28.000 --> 00:56:28.720
Kaew!

00:56:28.720 --> 00:56:29.400
Khun Yai!

00:56:29.400 --> 00:56:30.600
Kaew is in danger.

00:56:30.640 --> 00:56:31.520
You can’t go.

00:56:31.920 --> 00:56:32.720
Let me go!

00:56:33.480 --> 00:56:35.560
You want me to stand here and let that bastard hurt him?

00:56:42.640 --> 00:56:46.120
How dare you, scumbag!

00:56:52.880 --> 00:56:54.800
Khun Yai, are you in here?

00:57:09.480 --> 00:57:14.040
Let's wait and see what interesting story this episode four has.

00:57:14.160 --> 00:57:15.920
What will happen to Khun Yai?

00:57:15.920 --> 00:57:19.160
And what role will Chai play?

00:57:19.360 --> 00:57:25.400
He will play a big role in this episode,
because he will be the one to turn the tables.

00:57:47.840 --> 00:57:49.000
Good morning, Chai.

00:57:56.360 --> 00:57:58.800
Hello, it's Sophee.

00:57:59.560 --> 00:58:03.800
In this scene, I secretly followed Ruedee.

00:58:03.800 --> 00:58:07.960
I spied on the white house and met Kaewta.

00:58:08.200 --> 00:58:11.240
All the strong feelings of vengeance have returned.

00:58:11.240 --> 00:58:17.920
In my heart, if I went down there,
He'd be in trouble for sure.

00:58:17.920 --> 00:58:22.280
I'm starting to feel the heat inside.

00:58:22.800 --> 00:58:27.440
It's also very hot right now
I haven't turned on the air conditioner either.

00:58:27.560 --> 00:58:30.560
Fight! We've come this far, we have to fight.

00:58:30.880 --> 00:58:33.720
Don't forget to keep following to see what happens next.

00:58:37.320 --> 00:58:38.200
Let's go!

00:58:38.440 --> 00:58:39.160
Yes.

00:58:57.720 --> 00:59:00.400
How dare you walk all over this white house?

00:59:00.400 --> 00:59:02.720
I should have walked from over there.

00:59:03.720 --> 00:59:05.640
Who are you?

00:59:05.840 --> 00:59:07.960
I'm the one who should be asking who you are.

00:59:08.120 --> 00:59:10.720
How dare you walk all over this white house?

00:59:22.080 --> 00:59:25.800
Chai, this is Khun Yai and P' Saen.

00:59:28.720 --> 00:59:29.840
Nice to meet you.

00:59:35.520 --> 00:59:41.640
My name is Chai. I am Ruedee's older brother,
Kaewta's close friend.

00:59:42.080 --> 00:59:45.160
I just got back from Amsterdam.

01:00:02.800 --> 01:00:06.200
[Poem]
It's hard to break this sorrow, impossible to break it off.

01:00:06.400 --> 01:00:09.400
[Poem]
So many things I could cut, strangely,
but cutting this love is impossible, strangely.

01:00:10.200 --> 01:00:11.320
[Sigh]

01:00:11.400 --> 01:00:13.720
-Oh wow, you've been thinking for so long.
-Half a day!

01:00:14.040 --> 01:00:15.720
Stressed in this scene?

01:00:17.000 --> 01:00:18.640
Must be a relief.

01:00:18.720 --> 01:00:20.960
This scene has a Thai verse that I have to speak.

01:00:21.200 --> 01:00:23.800
And the poems from the old days, they were like...

01:00:24.160 --> 01:00:27.320
Breaking love is impossible to break off, I don't know what it is.

01:00:27.320 --> 01:00:31.440
I'm the one who's going to mess it up,
so I had to practice a bit.

01:00:31.560 --> 01:00:35.200
Otherwise, I'd be wasting the time of Khun Phra Nai
who is sitting there "Teh Jum."

01:00:36.280 --> 01:00:37.240
"Teh Jui"!

01:00:37.240 --> 01:00:38.200
-"Teh Jui."
-"Teh Jui."

01:00:38.960 --> 01:00:41.640
What is it, my lord? Why are you wearing a flower?

01:00:41.840 --> 01:00:45.280
I feel beautiful. P' Mai told me to feel beautiful.

01:00:45.280 --> 01:00:47.720
-[you have a sweet face.]
-He told me to feel beautiful.

01:00:47.840 --> 01:00:49.640
-You can pull it off.
-Or...

01:00:51.040 --> 01:00:54.240
Or maybe I'm... that doesn't seem right.

01:00:54.600 --> 01:00:56.960
-Is there a white envelope on the table?
-What am I?

01:01:03.360 --> 01:01:05.040
Are you stopping again, Uncle?

01:01:05.680 --> 01:01:08.000
If you make us stop dancing often,

